==English==

{{wikipedia}}
<center>[[Image:Leonardo God Adam.JPG|240px|Michaelangelo: The Creation|right]]</center>
===Etymology===
From Middle English < Old English '''god''' (supreme being, deity) < Old High German '''got''' (a rank of deity) < Proto-Germanic '''[[*guthan]]''' < Proto-Indo-European participle '''[[*ghut-]]''' (that which is invoked), from the PIE root '''[[*gheu(e)-]]''' (to call, to invoke). Not related to the word [[good]].

===Pronunciation===
*gŏd, {{IPAchar|/ɡɒd/}}, /<tt>gQd</tt>/
*{{audio|en-us-god.ogg|Audio (US)}}

===Proper noun===
'''God'''

# The single god of various [[monotheistic]] religions.
# The single male god of various [[duotheistic]] religions. <!-- eg Wicca -->
# An impersonal and universal spiritual presence or force.
# An omnipotent being, creator of the universe.

